(234, '_transient_ti_about_plugin_info_amp', 'O:8:\"stdClass\":22:{s:4:\"name\";s:3:\"AMP\";s:4:\"slug\";s:3:\"amp\";s:7:\"version\";s:5:\"1.5.2\";s:6:\"author\";s:95:\"<a href=\"https://github.com/ampproject/amp-wp/graphs/contributors\">AMP Project Contributors</a>\";s:14:\"author_profile\";s:41:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/automattic\";s:12:\"contributors\";a:9:{s:6:\"google\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:37:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/google\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:88:\"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/2adafb3bf578fd97d8d2ea1c2ccb3db3?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:6:\"Google\";}s:3:\"xwp\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:34:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/xwp\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:88:\"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/94486776b589f2de407f45c8c648e711?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:3:\"XWP\";}s:10:\"automattic\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:41:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/automattic\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:88:\"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/687b3bf96c41800814e3b93766444283?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:10:\"Automattic\";}s:11:\"westonruter\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:42:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/westonruter\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:88:\"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/989838a2534d491ccb184d5b8a654f99?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:12:\"Weston Ruter\";}s:13:\"albertomedina\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:44:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/albertomedina\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:88:\"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c61e7d8efedcd6e9bf7a0c6025f80489?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:13:\"albertomedina\";}s:10:\"schlessera\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:41:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/schlessera\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:88:\"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a686099e5d041a8825ef01d71513c2db?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:15:\"Alain Schlesser\";}s:10:\"swissspidy\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:41:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/swissspidy\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:88:\"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/609d6ee54dc13a51270cb99769535b82?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:15:\"Pascal Birchler\";}s:6:\"pierlo\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:37:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/pierlo\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:88:\"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4ac21eb950a17cd6abee28be7046cc7d?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:13:\"Pierre Gordon\";}s:12:\"ryankienstra\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:43:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/ryankienstra\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:88:\"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9056a7f3e47cce5f4f5c6bcf89cd8864?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:13:\"Ryan Kienstra\";}}s:12:\"requires_php\";s:3:\"5.6\";s:7:\"ratings\";a:5:{i:5;i:119;i:4;i:16;i:3;i:15;i:2;i:11;i:1;i:53;}s:11:\"num_ratings\";i:214;s:15:\"support_threads\";i:164;s:24:\"support_threads_resolved\";i:135;s:15:\"active_installs\";i:400000;s:8:\"homepage\";s:18:\"https://amp-wp.org\";s:8:\"sections\";a:6:{s:11:\"description\";s:3506:\"<p>The <a href=\"http://amp.dev\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">AMP Project</a> is an open-source initiative aiming to make the web better for all. AMP enables web experiences that are consistently fast, beautiful and high-performing across distribution platforms. AMP formerly stood for “Accelerated Mobile Pages”, but now works completely across desktop and mobile. The official AMP plugin for WordPress supports fully integrated AMP publishing for WordPress sites, with robust capabilities and granular publisher controls.</p>\n<p>Features and capabilities provided by the plugin include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>AMP-first Experiences</strong>: enabling <a href=\"https://amp.dev/about/websites\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">full-site AMP experiences</a> without sacrificing the flexibility of the platform or the fidelity of content.</li>\n<li><strong>Core Theme Support</strong>: enabling AMP compatibility for all core themes, from Twenty Ten all the way through Twenty Twenty.</li>\n<li><strong>Compatibility Tool</strong>: when automatic conversion of markup to AMP is not possible, debug AMP validation errors with detailed information including the invalid markup and the specific components responsible on site (e.g theme, plugin, embed); validation errors are shown contextually with their respective blocks in the editor.</li>\n<li><strong>CSS Tree Shaking</strong>: automatically remove the majority of unused CSS to bring the total under AMP&rsquo;s 75KB limit; when the total after tree shaking is still over this limit, prioritization is used so that the all-important theme stylesheet important is retained, leaving less important ones to be excluded (e.g. print styles).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Please note that the <a href=\"https://amp.dev/about/stories\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Stories</a> experience has been removed from the AMP plugin in favor of the feature being released as a standalone plugin. It will be available soon!</p>\n<p>The plugin can be configured to follow one of three different template modes: Standard, Transitional, and Reader. In Standard mode you use AMP as the framework for your site, and there need not be any separate AMP and non-AMP versions. When configured to operate in Reader and Transitional modes, a given page will have a canonical URL as well as a corresponding (paired) AMP URL. The AMP plugin is not serving as a mobile theme; it does not redirect mobile devices to the AMP version. Instead, the AMP version is served to mobile visitors when they find the content on platforms such as Twitter, Pinterest, Google Search, and others. Reader mode only supports serving AMP for singular posts, pages, and other post types, whereas Standard and Transitional mode support serving the entire site as AMP.</p>\n<p>With the official AMP plugin for WordPress, the WordPress ecosystem is provided with the capabilities and tools it needs to build world-class AMP experiences without deviating from its standard, flexible, and well-known content creation workflow.</p>\n<h3>Getting Started</h3>\n<p>To learn more about the plugin and start leveraging its capabilities to power your AMP content creation workflow check <a href=\"https://amp-wp.org\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">the official AMP plugin product site</a>.</p>\n<p>If you are a developer, we encourage you to <a href=\"https://github.com/ampproject/amp-wp\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">follow along</a> or <a href=\"https://github.com/ampproject/amp-wp/blob/develop/contributing.md\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">contribute</a> to the development of this plugin on GitHub.</p>\n\";s:12:\"installation\";s:432:\"<ol>\n<li>Téléversez le dossier dans le répertoire <code>/wp-content/plugins/</code>.</li>\n<li>Activez l’extension via le menu « Extensions » de WordPress.</li>\n<li>If you currently use older versions of the plugin in <code>Reader</code> mode, it is strongly encouraged to migrate to <code>Transitional</code> or <code>Standard</code> mode. Depending on your theme/plugins, some development work may be required.</li>\n</ol>\n\";s:3:\"faq\";s:420:\"<p>Please see the <a href=\"https://amp-wp.org/documentation/frequently-asked-questions/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">FAQs on amp-wp.org</a>. Don&rsquo;t see an answer to your question? Please <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/plugin/amp/\">search the support forum</a> to see if someone has asked your question. Otherwise, please <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/plugin/amp/#new-post\">open a new support topic</a>.</p>\n\";s:9:\"changelog\";s:156:\"<p>For the plugin’s changelog, please see <a href=\"https://github.com/ampproject/amp-wp/releases\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">the Releases page on GitHub</a>.</p>\n\";s:11:\"screenshots\";s:5732:\"<ol><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=2244151\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=2244151\" alt=\"In the website experience, theme support enables you to reuse the active theme&#039;s templates and stylesheets; all WordPress features (menus, widgets, comments) are available in AMP.\"></a><p>In the website experience, theme support enables you to reuse the active theme\'s templates and stylesheets; all WordPress features (menus, widgets, comments) are available in AMP.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-2.png?rev=2244151\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-2.png?rev=2244151\" alt=\"All core themes are supported, and many themes can be served as AMP with minimal changes, Otherwise, behavior is often as if JavaScript is turned off in the browser since scripts are removed.\"></a><p>All core themes are supported, and many themes can be served as AMP with minimal changes, Otherwise, behavior is often as if JavaScript is turned off in the browser since scripts are removed.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-3.png?rev=2244151\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-3.png?rev=2244151\" alt=\"Reader mode templates are still available, but they differ from the active theme.\"></a><p>Reader mode templates are still available, but they differ from the active theme.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-4.png?rev=2244151\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-4.png?rev=2244151\" alt=\"Switch from Reader mode to Transitional or Standard mode in AMP settings screen.\"></a><p>Switch from Reader mode to Transitional or Standard mode in AMP settings screen.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-5.png?rev=2244151\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-5.png?rev=2244151\" alt=\"Standard mode: Using AMP as the framework for your site, not having to maintain an AMP and non-AMP version. Mobile and desktop users get same experience.\"></a><p>Standard mode: Using AMP as the framework for your site, not having to maintain an AMP and non-AMP version. Mobile and desktop users get same experience.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-6.png?rev=2244151\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-6.png?rev=2244151\" alt=\"Transitional mode: A path to making your site fully AMP-compatible, with tools to assist with debugging validation issues along the way.\"></a><p>Transitional mode: A path to making your site fully AMP-compatible, with tools to assist with debugging validation issues along the way.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-7.png?rev=2244151\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-7.png?rev=2244151\" alt=\"Make the entire site available in AMP or pick specific post types and templates; you can also opt-out on per-post basis.\"></a><p>Make the entire site available in AMP or pick specific post types and templates; you can also opt-out on per-post basis.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-8.png?rev=2244151\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-8.png?rev=2244151\" alt=\"Plugin checks for AMP validity and will indicate when: no issues are found, new issues need review, or issues block AMP from being served.\"></a><p>Plugin checks for AMP validity and will indicate when: no issues are found, new issues need review, or issues block AMP from being served.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-9.png?rev=2244151\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-9.png?rev=2244151\" alt=\"The editor will surface validation issues during content authoring. The specific blocks with validation errors are indicated.\"></a><p>The editor will surface validation issues during content authoring. The specific blocks with validation errors are indicated.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-10.png?rev=2244151\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-10.png?rev=2244151\" alt=\"Each Validated URL shows the list of validation errors encountered, giving control over whether invalid markup is removed or kept. Keeping invalid markup disables AMP.\"></a><p>Each Validated URL shows the list of validation errors encountered, giving control over whether invalid markup is removed or kept. Keeping invalid markup disables AMP.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-11.png?rev=2244151\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-11.png?rev=2244151\" alt=\"Each validation error provides a stack trace to identify which code is responsible for the invalid markup, whether a theme, plugin, embed, content block, and so on.\"></a><p>Each validation error provides a stack trace to identify which code is responsible for the invalid markup, whether a theme, plugin, embed, content block, and so on.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-12.png?rev=2244151\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-12.png?rev=2244151\" alt=\"Styles added by themes and plugins are automatically concatenated, minified, and tree-shaken to try to keep the total under 75KB of inline CSS.\"></a><p>Styles added by themes and plugins are automatically concatenated, minified, and tree-shaken to try to keep the total under 75KB of inline CSS.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-13.png?rev=2244151\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-13.png?rev=2244151\" alt=\"A WP-CLI command is provided to check the URLs on a site for AMP validity. Results are available in the admin for inspection.\"></a><p>A WP-CLI command is provided to check the URLs on a site for AMP validity. Results are available in the admin for inspection.</p></li></ol>\";s:7:\"reviews\";s:14974:\"<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Perfection!</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 sur 5 étoiles\" data-title-template=\"%s sur 5 étoiles\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Par <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/arafail\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/995a16c6d624d85feb736089b858ae07?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/995a16c6d624d85feb736089b858ae07?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/arafail\" class=\"reviewer-name\">arafail</a> le <span class=\"review-date\">avril 8, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">This plugin is perfect! Very easy to install and use and it works with out a flaw.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Not Great.</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 sur 5 étoiles\" data-title-template=\"%s sur 5 étoiles\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Par <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/bricmor\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/150ca09b445cbf200e025b2498e514e7?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/150ca09b445cbf200e025b2498e514e7?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/bricmor\" class=\"reviewer-name\">darrynbrick <small>(bricmor)</small></a> le <span class=\"review-date\">avril 7, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Continuous errors not syncing with Google disallowing site to be added to ad sense without a fix.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Best AMP Plugin for WordPress Sites</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 sur 5 étoiles\" data-title-template=\"%s sur 5 étoiles\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Par <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/divakaraganesh\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/55eba904ea9353d1973a206bd9a8125a?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/55eba904ea9353d1973a206bd9a8125a?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/divakaraganesh\" class=\"reviewer-name\">divakaraganesh</a> le <span class=\"review-date\">avril 7, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I am using this Plugin form past 1 year on multiple sites. I can say this is the best plugin if you want to implement AMP on WordPress site. \n\nThe plugin team is very supportive. They respond to support tickets instantly most of the time.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Best AMP plugin ever!</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 sur 5 étoiles\" data-title-template=\"%s sur 5 étoiles\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Par <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/nikitasp\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/630a18bb4ed95c4e82b1b9c0fb285204?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/630a18bb4ed95c4e82b1b9c0fb285204?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/nikitasp\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Nikita_Sp <small>(Nikita.Sp)</small></a> le <span class=\"review-date\">avril 4, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Google always invent something new and try to make internet better, faster, more clear.\nOne of the current new features is AMP. I don\'t know if it become a new trend of website building, but it\'s clear we should add AMP support for our websites where it\'s possible.\n\nI think <strong>this is the best and FREE plugin for WordPress website to make your site AMP support</strong>.\n\nSpecial thanks to @westonruter for his help I appreciate, with developing custom themes for this plugin and it\'s update.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Outstanding AMP Plugin - Top Notch Support!</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 sur 5 étoiles\" data-title-template=\"%s sur 5 étoiles\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Par <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/tuxmob\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/27b8826e9a7b77d3d3994ae8a9ebc77b?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/27b8826e9a7b77d3d3994ae8a9ebc77b?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/tuxmob\" class=\"reviewer-name\">tuxmob</a> le <span class=\"review-date\">avril 4, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I had an issue with google search console:\n\nThe attribute \'tabindex\' in tag \'span\' is missing or incorrect, but required by attribute \'on\'.\n\nI posted my issue this morning (Saturday) and within minuets, Weston was there to my rescue, asking for some clarification and then providing me a lightning fast and Verified fix. \n\nThank You Development Team, and thank you Weston for your Top Notch Support!!!</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Best support ever! also best amp plugin withouth any doubt</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 sur 5 étoiles\" data-title-template=\"%s sur 5 étoiles\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Par <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/jorgitobg\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/be2955d6b8c103f7121557178b2b050e?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/be2955d6b8c103f7121557178b2b050e?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/jorgitobg\" class=\"reviewer-name\">jorgitobg</a> le <span class=\"review-date\">mars 28, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Im sure you will try other AMP plugins as I did, but you will waste time.\nThis is the best plugin by far, and also best fastest support you will receive ever.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Great plugin and a very responsive and helpful support</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 sur 5 étoiles\" data-title-template=\"%s sur 5 étoiles\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Par <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/asafm7\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f8bff18e4398191eec929cdd86604af7?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f8bff18e4398191eec929cdd86604af7?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/asafm7\" class=\"reviewer-name\">asafm7</a> le <span class=\"review-date\">mars 25, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">One of the best support experiences I had with a free tool.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Succesful Validation</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 sur 5 étoiles\" data-title-template=\"%s sur 5 étoiles\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Par <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/lenav7\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/7ca02da694159447bcdd5ba83e01e364?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/7ca02da694159447bcdd5ba83e01e364?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/lenav7\" class=\"reviewer-name\">lenav7</a> le <span class=\"review-date\">mars 19, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">After installing this plugin and great guidance from this team, my site has improved its speed and I am a satisfied AMP plugin user. Thank you very much!</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Great support</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 sur 5 étoiles\" data-title-template=\"%s sur 5 étoiles\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Par <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/rsmith4321\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/6951e6b98baf092010f3461f71229f64?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/6951e6b98baf092010f3461f71229f64?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/rsmith4321\" class=\"reviewer-name\">rsmith4321</a> le <span class=\"review-date\">mars 9, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Every time I have an issue with the plugin or a question I get a reply within a day from a Google engineer. The support is fantastic. </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Very stable and reliable AMP plugin with top notch support</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 sur 5 étoiles\" data-title-template=\"%s sur 5 étoiles\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Par <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/schwifty5\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9eb5c7bc09314732885f396b54b4439b?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9eb5c7bc09314732885f396b54b4439b?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/schwifty5\" class=\"reviewer-name\">schwifty5</a> le <span class=\"review-date\">mars 6, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I am using this plugin for AMP on multiple big websites with customized templates. It is working very stable and reliable and is in my opinion the best plugin for AMP out there.\n\nIt does not come with unnecessary bloat and has a well thought out and clean code structure.\n\nI experienced a very quick and professional support, even though the issue I once had was not from the AMP plugin itself, but from custom code.\n\nI absolutely recommend this plugin if you are looking to implement AMP into websites. You will not find a more professional solution as this one.</div>\n</div>\n\";}s:17:\"short_description\";s:144:\"Official AMP plugin, supported by the AMP team. Formerly Accelerated Mobile Pages, AMP enables great experiences across both mobile and desktop.\";s:13:\"download_link\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.1.5.2.zip\";s:11:\"screenshots\";a:13:{i:1;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=2244151\";s:7:\"caption\";s:179:\"In the website experience, theme support enables you to reuse the active theme\'s templates and stylesheets; all WordPress features (menus, widgets, comments) are available in AMP.\";}i:2;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-2.png?rev=2244151\";s:7:\"caption\";s:191:\"All core themes are supported, and many themes can be served as AMP with minimal changes, Otherwise, behavior is often as if JavaScript is turned off in the browser since scripts are removed.\";}i:3;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-3.png?rev=2244151\";s:7:\"caption\";s:81:\"Reader mode templates are still available, but they differ from the active theme.\";}i:4;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-4.png?rev=2244151\";s:7:\"caption\";s:80:\"Switch from Reader mode to Transitional or Standard mode in AMP settings screen.\";}i:5;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-5.png?rev=2244151\";s:7:\"caption\";s:153:\"Standard mode: Using AMP as the framework for your site, not having to maintain an AMP and non-AMP version. Mobile and desktop users get same experience.\";}i:6;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-6.png?rev=2244151\";s:7:\"caption\";s:136:\"Transitional mode: A path to making your site fully AMP-compatible, with tools to assist with debugging validation issues along the way.\";}i:7;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-7.png?rev=2244151\";s:7:\"caption\";s:120:\"Make the entire site available in AMP or pick specific post types and templates; you can also opt-out on per-post basis.\";}i:8;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-8.png?rev=2244151\";s:7:\"caption\";s:138:\"Plugin checks for AMP validity and will indicate when: no issues are found, new issues need review, or issues block AMP from being served.\";}i:9;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-9.png?rev=2244151\";s:7:\"caption\";s:125:\"The editor will surface validation issues during content authoring. The specific blocks with validation errors are indicated.\";}i:10;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:57:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-10.png?rev=2244151\";s:7:\"caption\";s:167:\"Each Validated URL shows the list of validation errors encountered, giving control over whether invalid markup is removed or kept. Keeping invalid markup disables AMP.\";}i:11;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:57:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-11.png?rev=2244151\";s:7:\"caption\";s:164:\"Each validation error provides a stack trace to identify which code is responsible for the invalid markup, whether a theme, plugin, embed, content block, and so on.\";}i:12;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:57:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-12.png?rev=2244151\";s:7:\"caption\";s:143:\"Styles added by themes and plugins are automatically concatenated, minified, and tree-shaken to try to keep the total under 75KB of inline CSS.\";}i:13;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:57:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-13.png?rev=2244151\";s:7:\"caption\";s:125:\"A WP-CLI command is provided to check the URLs on a site for AMP validity. Results are available in the admin for inspection.\";}}s:8:\"versions\";a:35:{s:3:\"0.2\";s:50:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.2.zip\";s:3:\"0.3\";s:50:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.3.zip\";s:5:\"0.3.1\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.3.1.zip\";s:5:\"0.3.2\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.3.2.zip\";s:5:\"0.3.3\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.3.3.zip\";s:3:\"0.4\";s:50:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.4.zip\";s:5:\"0.4.1\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.4.1.zip\";s:5:\"0.4.2\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.4.2.zip\";s:3:\"0.5\";s:50:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.5.zip\";s:5:\"0.5.1\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.5.1.zip\";s:5:\"0.6.0\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.6.0.zip\";s:5:\"0.6.1\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.6.1.zip\";s:5:\"0.6.2\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.6.2.zip\";s:5:\"0.7.0\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.7.0.zip\";s:5:\"0.7.1\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.7.1.zip\";s:5:\"0.7.2\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.7.2.zip\";s:5:\"1.0.0\";s:52:\"https://downl